- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The study uses a multi-clinical information system large-scale database to build models, which involves computational engineering and science. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper utilizes artificial intelligence techniques such as attention-based recurrent neural networks to predict the response to fluid bolus therapy among hypotensive patients in ICUs. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The study uses neural network algorithms such as long short term memory network (LSTM) and gated recurrent units network (GRU) to build models. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The study aims to provide clinical interpretability of the models, which involves understanding the interaction between humans and computers in a healthcare setting.
